      <hedline>
        <hl1>Low Price in British Energy Privatization</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">Reuters</byline>
      <dateline>LONDON, July 14</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The British Government learned today that it would receive L1.41 billion, or  $2.19 billion, from a sell-off of most of Britain's nuclear power plants -- barely half what it expected when it announced the sale plan in March.</p>
        <p>BZW Securities, the stockbrokers acting for the Government, said individual  Britons who applied for shares in British Energy P.L.C. would pay a total of 198 pence, or $3.08, a share, and institutional investors 203 pence, or $3.15, both  in two stages. Trading in the shares begins Monday.</p>
      </block>
